00:48:36,841 --> 00:48:37,981
This is insane.

1519
00:48:37,981 --> 00:48:39,481
It's lightly sour.

1520
00:48:40,351 --> 00:48:41,511
I can see why it's so popular.

1521
00:48:41,511 --> 00:48:42,751
Really? Is it what you expected?

1522
00:48:42,751 --> 00:48:43,751
It has to be popular.

1523
00:48:43,751 --> 00:48:47,191
It's a taste that young people would love.

1524
00:48:47,191 --> 00:48:49,391
- It's the taste of Korea.
- It's very delicious.

1525
00:48:49,391 --> 00:48:51,021
- Sometimes, - It's savory too.

1526
00:48:51,021 --> 00:48:52,691
we make bibimbap in brass bowls.

1527
00:48:52,691 --> 00:48:55,131
We add gochujang, sesame oil,

1528
00:48:55,131 --> 00:48:56,731
leftover vegetables at home,

1529
00:48:56,731 --> 00:48:58,061
and seasoned vegetables.

1530
00:48:58,561 --> 00:49:00,971
Due to the heavy taste of gochujang,

1531
00:49:01,471 --> 00:49:02,971
- it can be a little heavy.
- Right.

1532
00:49:02,971 --> 00:49:04,801
However, this is very refreshing.

1533
00:49:04,801 --> 00:49:06,211
It's also like a salad.

1534
00:49:06,241 --> 00:49:08,071
- Right.
- It goes well with rice.

1535
00:49:09,081 --> 00:49:10,641
You eat bibimbap for the sesame oil flavor.

1536
00:49:10,941 --> 00:49:12,781
With spring cabbage, you don't need anything else.

1537
00:49:12,781 --> 00:49:15,311
- This is very refreshing.
- You only need this.

1538
00:49:15,351 --> 00:49:17,021
- I don't want to add any eggs.
- So...

1539
00:49:17,021 --> 00:49:18,421
- I don't want to mix eggs.
- Right.

1540
00:49:18,481 --> 00:49:21,051
One should definitely learn how to season...

1541
00:49:21,051 --> 00:49:23,261
- spring cabbages.
- Absolutely.

1542
00:49:23,261 --> 00:49:25,291
- You should have your own recipe.
- Definitely.

1543
00:49:25,291 --> 00:49:26,931
I should learn how to cook.

1544
00:49:26,931 --> 00:49:28,091
(We'll reveal the recipe only to our viewers.)

1545
00:49:28,091 --> 00:49:29,601
The spring cabbage is endless.

1546
00:49:29,601 --> 00:49:30,761
(It's time to capture the screen.)

1547
00:49:30,761 --> 00:49:33,131
- It tastes marvelous.
- It's not spicy either.

1548
00:49:33,131 --> 00:49:34,201
All the dishes are delicious today.

1549
00:49:34,201 --> 00:49:35,871
This is the best bibimbap I ever had.

1550
00:49:35,871 --> 00:49:36,901
(The undisputed number 1 among all bibimbap)

1551
00:49:36,901 --> 00:49:39,071
- It's unrivaled.
- I like today's menu.

1552
00:49:39,341 --> 00:49:41,911
- It's very healthy.
- Water parsley...

1553
00:49:41,911 --> 00:49:43,841
and spring cabbage blend well in the dish.

1554
00:49:43,841 --> 00:49:45,281
(Now is the time for Mr. Moon, the eating master.)

1555
00:49:45,281 --> 00:49:47,611
I didn't eat any rice. I was waiting to eat this.

1556
00:49:47,681 --> 00:49:50,251
I must say that it's a unique experience.

1557
00:49:51,851 --> 00:49:57,121
(The world of spring spreads all over the palate.)

1558
00:50:03,961 --> 00:50:05,931
- Joon and I always ate together.
- Have more rice.

1559
00:50:06,201 --> 00:50:07,271
Are you done already?

1560
00:50:07,971 --> 00:50:10,641
Gosh, did you finish that?

1561
00:50:11,901 --> 00:50:13,711
Mind your own business. I'm working.

1562
00:50:13,711 --> 00:50:14,741
(Eating is my job.)

1563
00:50:17,381 --> 00:50:18,441
He's eating with gusto.

1564
00:50:18,881 --> 00:50:19,881
(Shouting)

1565
00:50:20,711 --> 00:50:22,681
It tastes better than meat in the spring.

1566
00:50:22,681 --> 00:50:23,751
(The cabbage tastes better than meat.)

1567
00:50:25,221 --> 00:50:26,291
My gosh.

1568
00:50:26,291 --> 00:50:27,691
(Sadly, he has one spoonful left.)

1569
00:50:27,951 --> 00:50:29,021
Goodness.

1570
00:50:29,821 --> 00:50:31,061
I finished already.

1571
00:50:32,591 --> 00:50:34,331
(Laying a piece of spring cabbage)

1572
00:50:34,331 --> 00:50:36,501
(Covering with an egg blanket)

1573
00:50:36,731 --> 00:50:37,861
Seriously?

1574
00:50:38,871 --> 00:50:40,431
- It's his last bite.
- Oh, my.

1575
00:50:40,431 --> 00:50:41,471
See you next year.

1576
00:50:42,741 --> 00:50:43,971
(Anticipating)

1577
00:50:43,971 --> 00:50:45,071
We'll see it next year.

1578
00:50:45,841 --> 00:50:46,841
We'll see it next year.

1579
00:50:52,881 --> 00:50:54,181
That was magnificent.

1580
00:50:54,181 --> 00:50:55,451
(It was mesmerizing.)

1581
00:50:55,451 --> 00:50:56,781
His way of eating is fun.

1582
00:50:58,081 --> 00:50:59,421
That's why we watch people eat on TV.

1583
00:50:59,421 --> 00:51:00,751
- His eating is interesting.
- Yes.

1584
00:51:01,191 --> 00:51:03,191
He's a professional. He gets paid to eat.

1585
00:51:04,661 --> 00:51:06,391
(The end)

1586
00:51:10,061 --> 00:51:11,901
An instant blood sugar spike.

1587
00:51:12,131 --> 00:51:13,131
He got it right away.

1588
00:51:13,131 --> 00:51:14,601
(There's spring inside me.)

1589
00:51:15,201 --> 00:51:17,101
We had a lot of food today.

1590
00:51:17,101 --> 00:51:18,171
It was a great meal.

1591
00:51:18,171 --> 00:51:20,141
All five of us ate too much today.

1592
00:51:20,141 --> 00:51:21,441
- We really did.
- It was our first time.

1593
00:51:21,641 --> 00:51:22,781
I'm so full.

1594
00:51:23,011 --> 00:51:25,181
We also have a dessert for you.

1595
00:51:25,181 --> 00:51:26,711
- No way.
- Really?

1596
00:51:26,851 --> 00:51:28,381
Is it sikhye? What is it?

1597
00:51:28,751 --> 00:51:30,451
- Here you go.
- It's half-ripe persimmon.

1598
00:51:30,481 --> 00:51:32,051
There's one for each of you.

1599
00:51:32,051 --> 00:51:33,651
(Nicely plated desserts arrive.)

1600
00:51:33,651 --> 00:51:34,721
Are they frozen?

1601
00:51:35,051 --> 00:51:36,161
(It looks beautiful.)

1602
00:51:36,161 --> 00:51:37,691
- Are they frozen?
- This looks so good.

1603
00:51:37,691 --> 00:51:38,761
Is this...

1604
00:51:38,761 --> 00:51:40,191
- fine dining or what?
- It's frozen.

1605
00:51:40,291 --> 00:51:41,461
Is it frozen persimmon?

1606
00:51:41,591 --> 00:51:42,661
Why...

1607
00:51:43,301 --> 00:51:46,001
- It's fine dining.
- Why are you giving it to us?

1608
00:51:46,701 --> 00:51:48,431
- Everyone.
- This is really delicious.

1609
00:51:48,501 --> 00:51:50,541
These are frozen persimmons made with...

1610
00:51:50,541 --> 00:51:52,001
- Really?
- semi-dried Cheongdo persimmons.

1611
00:51:52,001 --> 00:51:53,371
- Oh, my.
- Goodness.

1612
00:51:53,611 --> 00:51:54,971
This is my favorite.

1613
00:51:55,271 --> 00:51:56,311
It reminds me of school.

1614
00:51:56,311 --> 00:51:57,311
(Brilliant and moist)

1615
00:51:57,581 --> 00:51:59,211
- Can we eat it?
- Did you get one each?

1616
00:51:59,211 --> 00:52:00,481
- Yes.
- Can't we eat it?

1617
00:52:00,511 --> 00:52:01,651
It's a game, isn't it?

1618
00:52:02,821 --> 00:52:03,981
It must be a game.

1619
00:52:04,621 --> 00:52:05,951
- Just eat it.
- You may eat it.

1620
00:52:05,951 --> 00:52:07,451
We can eat it? Here I go.

1621
00:52:07,451 --> 00:52:08,621
It must be a game.

1622
00:52:08,861 --> 00:52:10,821
- No, it's not.
- Mine is a persimmon.

1623
00:52:11,461 --> 00:52:12,461
Mine is a persimmon.

1624
00:52:12,461 --> 00:52:14,091
(Being cautious with his taste buds)

1625
00:52:14,091 --> 00:52:15,091
It's a persimmon.

1626
00:52:25,071 --> 00:52:27,141
(Did you get a bad one?)

1627
00:52:28,741 --> 00:52:30,941
It's so delicious.

1628
00:52:31,641 --> 00:52:33,011
- It's very good.
- Is it a persimmon?

1629
00:52:33,011 --> 00:52:34,111
- Yes.
- Yes.

1630
00:52:34,111 --> 00:52:36,121
You know what?

1631
00:52:36,121 --> 00:52:38,651
What we ate today deserves one Michelin star.

1632
00:52:38,651 --> 00:52:41,651
- Really?
- The spring cabbage...

1633
00:52:41,651 --> 00:52:43,261
- and water parsley jeon.
- They were amazing.

1634
00:52:43,261 --> 00:52:46,391
These three dishes were very Korean...

1635
00:52:46,391 --> 00:52:47,791
and nice at the same time.

1636
00:52:47,791 --> 00:52:49,361
This meal deserves an award.

1637
00:52:49,361 --> 00:52:50,731
- Foreigners would love it too.
- Yes.

1638
00:52:50,731 --> 00:52:52,531
And the persimmon as a dessert at the end.

1639
00:52:52,531 --> 00:52:54,401
- It was perfect.
- The persimmon tastes so good.

1640
00:52:54,731 --> 00:52:55,941
It's really good.

1641
00:52:56,301 --> 00:52:57,301
Why did they give it to us?

1642
00:52:57,601 --> 00:52:59,611
- The bowls are different.
- All bowls are different.

1643
00:52:59,611 --> 00:53:01,711
(Each persimmon bowl was different.)

1644
00:53:01,711 --> 00:53:04,241
Take a look underneath your bowl.

1645
00:53:04,241 --> 00:53:05,541
- What?
- What?

1646
00:53:06,381 --> 00:53:08,551
(I don't see anything.)

1647
00:53:08,551 --> 00:53:09,551
I mean...

1648
00:53:10,381 --> 00:53:11,381
I mean...

1649
00:53:11,381 --> 00:53:12,591
Jong Min, why aren't you saying anything?

1650
00:53:12,791 --> 00:53:14,321
- What?
- Goodness.

1651
00:53:14,321 --> 00:53:15,451
He got it. What is it?

1652
00:53:15,451 --> 00:53:16,761
- Seriously?
- What do you have?

1653
00:53:17,061 --> 00:53:18,621
I don't think it's a bad thing.

1654
00:53:18,621 --> 00:53:20,031
He's insanely lucky.

1655
00:53:20,161 --> 00:53:21,291
What is it?

1656
00:53:22,361 --> 00:53:25,001
- It's a four-leaf clover.
- Congratulations, Jong Min.

1657
00:53:25,031 --> 00:53:26,131
What?

1658
00:53:26,131 --> 00:53:27,631
(Congratulations)

1659
00:53:27,631 --> 00:53:29,341
You will go and pick spring cabbages now.

1660
00:53:30,141 --> 00:53:32,771
All right, Jong Min is...

1661
00:53:32,911 --> 00:53:33,911
Goodness.

1662
00:53:34,271 --> 00:53:36,611
- He's about to get lucky.
- I'm so jealous.

1663
00:53:37,411 --> 00:53:39,351
I don't care about that. The persimmon is so good.

1664
00:53:40,181 --> 00:53:43,321
We will call you outside once we finish setting up.

1665
00:53:43,321 --> 00:53:44,681
- Okay.
- I ate too much.

1666
00:53:46,191 --> 00:53:48,051
What? There are gift boxes.

1667
00:53:49,191 --> 00:53:50,791
(Anticipating)

1668
00:53:51,691 --> 00:53:53,761
- There are four.
- What's this?

1669
00:53:54,131 --> 00:53:55,191
What is it?

1670
00:53:55,831 --> 00:53:56,931
- What is it?
- What's going on?

1671
00:53:57,161 --> 00:53:58,661
What's all this?

1672
00:53:59,301 --> 00:54:01,031
(Behind the mysterious gift boxes)

1673
00:54:01,471 --> 00:54:04,171
(A bunch of unidentifiable items)

1674
00:54:04,701 --> 00:54:06,971
What are we doing? Will it require strength?

1675
00:54:07,811 --> 00:54:09,841
I'm too full to move.

1676
00:54:10,041 --> 00:54:11,241
Everyone.

1677
00:54:11,741 --> 00:54:12,951
Did you enjoy your meal?

1678
00:54:12,951 --> 00:54:14,211
- Yes.
- It was great.

1679
00:54:14,281 --> 00:54:16,651
You also had frozen persimmons at the end.

1680
00:54:16,651 --> 00:54:17,651
- Yes.
- Yes.

1681
00:54:17,651 --> 00:54:20,451
Jong Min found a four-leaf clover.

1682
00:54:20,451 --> 00:54:21,551
Yes, I did.

1683
00:54:21,551 --> 00:54:25,321
Jong Min who picked the lucky four-leaf clover.

1684
00:54:25,321 --> 00:54:26,731
- Yes?
- Does he get to sleep indoors?

1685
00:54:26,831 --> 00:54:27,961
Tonight...

1686
00:54:28,691 --> 00:54:29,761
No way.

1687
00:54:30,931 --> 00:54:32,731
- No way.
- You'll sleep indoors tonight.

1688
00:54:32,731 --> 00:54:34,431
- Seriously?
- What?

1689
00:54:35,701 --> 00:54:36,971
But I didn't do anything.

1690
00:54:38,301 --> 00:54:39,641
(The reality hits.)

1691
00:54:39,641 --> 00:54:42,781
- He's ridiculously lucky.
- This is annoying.

1692
00:54:42,781 --> 00:54:44,441
- All I did was eat a persimmon.
- I can't believe this.

1693
00:54:44,441 --> 00:54:45,441
Unbelievable.

1694
00:54:45,441 --> 00:54:47,551
On top of that, you took the one that I left.

1695
00:54:47,551 --> 00:54:49,551
I was about to grab a bowl,

1696
00:54:49,551 --> 00:54:50,681
but DinDin took it away from me.

1697
00:54:52,151 --> 00:54:54,791
(He went after the one closest to him but failed.)

1698
00:54:55,321 --> 00:54:57,761
(He took the second closest.)

1699
00:54:57,821 --> 00:54:58,821
Is it confirmed?

1700
00:54:58,821 --> 00:55:00,691
- Yes, it's confirmed.
- This is so shocking.

1701
00:55:00,691 --> 00:55:02,191
Someone must be telling him.

1702
00:55:02,401 --> 00:55:03,831
"Take that one."

1703
00:55:04,361 --> 00:55:06,401
Are you possessed by a spirit?

1704
00:55:07,071 --> 00:55:08,131
How could this happen?

1705
00:55:08,371 --> 00:55:11,171
- What is he going to do?
- Jong Min will sleep indoors.

1706
00:55:11,901 --> 00:55:13,441
- Instead, - Instead?

1707
00:55:13,441 --> 00:55:15,741
- Instead?
- you'll be the tagger.

1708
00:55:15,741 --> 00:55:16,741
(Jong Min will be the tagger.)

1709
00:55:16,741 --> 00:55:18,241
Okay, I'll do anything.

1710
00:55:19,381 --> 00:55:22,381
- My goodness.
- This must be something intense.

1711
00:55:22,381 --> 00:55:23,421
All right, everyone.

1712
00:55:23,551 --> 00:55:25,521
Tonight's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors is...

1713
00:55:26,021 --> 00:55:27,851
The Way to Sleeping Indoors.

1714
00:55:28,591 --> 00:55:30,691
- The Way to Sleeping Indoors?
- Yes.

1715
00:55:30,691 --> 00:55:34,091
You must go through every bedtime course.

1716
00:55:34,091 --> 00:55:36,301
You will play Red Light Green Light.

1717
00:55:36,301 --> 00:55:37,361
(Red Light Green Light while completing the mission)

1718
00:55:37,631 --> 00:55:40,971
(They must play Red Light Green Light while getting ready for bed.)

1719
00:55:40,971 --> 00:55:43,601
I will explain each bedtime course.

1720
00:55:43,771 --> 00:55:46,271
The first course is putting on pajamas.

1721
00:55:46,971 --> 00:55:49,011
Pick 1 of the 4 boxes.

1722
00:55:49,641 --> 00:55:52,011
Change into the pajamas inside your box.

1723
00:55:52,711 --> 00:55:53,881
Are they in every size?

1724
00:55:53,881 --> 00:55:54,981
(Get changed into each person's pajamas.)

1725
00:55:54,981 --> 00:55:56,681
His size is different from mine.

1726
00:55:56,781 --> 00:55:59,051
If there's a robe in Se Yoon's size,

1727
00:55:59,051 --> 00:56:00,851
it would reach my feet.

1728
00:56:01,151 --> 00:56:02,661
You'll find them in your size.

1729
00:56:03,621 --> 00:56:06,061
The second course is washing your feet.

1730
00:56:06,661 --> 00:56:09,961
This course involves a foot bath...

1731
00:56:09,961 --> 00:56:11,461
filled with iced water.

1732
00:56:11,461 --> 00:56:13,401
(A foot bath with iced water)

1733
00:56:13,571 --> 00:56:15,101
When the tagger turns around,

1734
00:56:15,471 --> 00:56:17,301
you must be inside the basin.

1735
00:56:17,301 --> 00:56:18,541
- I see.
- Right.

1736
00:56:18,541 --> 00:56:20,741
It's okay if one of your feet is inside the basin,

1737
00:56:20,741 --> 00:56:22,941
but the other foot can't touch the ground.

1738
00:56:22,941 --> 00:56:24,181
I understand.

1739
00:56:24,741 --> 00:56:26,711
- The third course is...
- This is difficult.

1740
00:56:26,711 --> 00:56:28,751
- drinking tea for good night.
- What?

1741
00:56:29,181 --> 00:56:32,081
(Tea bags are hanging on the pull-up bar.)

1742
00:56:32,491 --> 00:56:34,021
You will put a water cup on your head.

1743
00:56:34,021 --> 00:56:35,051
(They put a water cup on their head.)

1744
00:56:35,191 --> 00:56:38,321
You must put the tea bag in the cup by adjusting the rope...

1745
00:56:38,861 --> 00:56:40,331
attached to the pulley with your toes.

1746
00:56:40,661 --> 00:56:42,761
Once you drink up the tea,

1747
00:56:42,761 --> 00:56:43,861
- We have to drink it up?
- you succeed.

1748
00:56:44,131 --> 00:56:46,501
Then there's the fourth course, wearing the blindfold.

1749
00:56:46,701 --> 00:56:47,701
What?

1750
00:56:47,701 --> 00:56:50,141
You should choose one blindfold and put it on your face.

1751
00:56:50,141 --> 00:56:51,371
It must be ink.

1752
00:56:51,371 --> 00:56:53,171
If you pick a blindfold soaked in water, you pass.

1753
00:56:53,741 --> 00:56:56,741
(Among the 5 blindfolds, 3 are soaked with ink.)

1754
00:56:57,011 --> 00:56:59,151
The last course is the Return Home Zone.

1755
00:56:59,351 --> 00:57:02,881
If you open the door, go in, and close the door, you succeed.

1756
00:57:02,951 --> 00:57:05,081
- Two people will sleep indoors.
- Okay.

1757
00:57:05,081 --> 00:57:07,891
- So, we have to go in quickly.
- Yes. It's 1st come, 1st served.

1758
00:57:08,121 --> 00:57:09,321
I'll just sleep outdoors.

1759
00:57:09,661 --> 00:57:10,661
- This is impossible.
- Can I just...

1760
00:57:10,661 --> 00:57:12,591
- give up quickly...
- How would we do all these things?

1761
00:57:12,591 --> 00:57:14,491
and sleep outdoors?

1762
00:57:14,691 --> 00:57:16,831
This is just too tough.

1763
00:57:16,831 --> 00:57:17,961
This is like a triathlon.

1764
00:57:17,961 --> 00:57:19,331
(They have to do all these things, playing Red Light Green Light.)

1765
00:57:19,371 --> 00:57:21,471
If you get caught by the tagger, you have to go back...

1766
00:57:21,471 --> 00:57:23,841
to the second course, the feet-washing zone.

1767
00:57:23,841 --> 00:57:24,841
(The Ice Water Inferno returns.)

1768
