2519
01:26:53,589 --> 01:26:56,119
I should put the sickle deep underneath to cut it.

2520
01:26:56,119 --> 01:26:58,289
But it shouldn't be too deep.

2521
01:26:58,529 --> 01:26:59,999
The soil will come up with it like this.

2522
01:26:59,999 --> 01:27:01,229
- You're right.
- See?

2523
01:27:01,229 --> 01:27:03,069
- This is difficult.
- You don't want to do that.

2524
01:27:03,069 --> 01:27:05,069
So, here's the trick.

2525
01:27:05,229 --> 01:27:07,099
You should hold the sickle like this.

2526
01:27:07,099 --> 01:27:08,499
Place it on the ground like this.

2527
01:27:08,499 --> 01:27:09,869
- Don't press it too hard.
- Okay.

2528
01:27:09,869 --> 01:27:11,939
Lift it slightly off the ground and place it like this.

2529
01:27:11,939 --> 01:27:13,209
- Lift it up.
- How?

2530
01:27:13,509 --> 01:27:15,179
Place it like this and lift it up.

2531
01:27:15,509 --> 01:27:16,949
- Like this?
- Exactly.

2532
01:27:17,049 --> 01:27:19,249
- Lift it up slightly and cut it.
- Then cut it.

2533
01:27:19,249 --> 01:27:20,779
- Okay.
- Cut it.

2534
01:27:20,779 --> 01:27:22,219
- Okay.
- Do you understand?

2535
01:27:22,219 --> 01:27:23,989
- I'll give it a try.
- Try it.

2536
01:27:23,989 --> 01:27:25,219
The amount is...

2537
01:27:26,049 --> 01:27:29,019
If we fill 3 baskets, it will be 30kg.

2538
01:27:29,019 --> 01:27:30,189
- It's 30kg.
- Okay.

2539
01:27:30,189 --> 01:27:32,929
But looking at what you're doing now...

2540
01:27:32,929 --> 01:27:35,029
I told you not to cut off the nodes, but you cut them.

2541
01:27:35,029 --> 01:27:36,599
You shouldn't do that.

2542
01:27:37,199 --> 01:27:38,499
You have to keep the nodes intact.

2543
01:27:38,499 --> 01:27:39,869
- Keep the nodes.
- The nodes here.

2544
01:27:40,139 --> 01:27:41,599
I placed it close to the ground, though.

2545
01:27:42,269 --> 01:27:44,009
The nodes... Let me see.

2546
01:27:44,009 --> 01:27:45,869
See? You cut off the nodes.

2547
01:27:46,139 --> 01:27:49,379
(Jong Min starts harvesting the water parsley.)

2548
01:27:49,549 --> 01:27:51,409
Sir, how about this?

2549
01:27:51,409 --> 01:27:52,409
What?

2550
01:27:52,919 --> 01:27:54,649
- That's good.
- It looks good.

2551
01:27:54,779 --> 01:27:58,019
This is what you do. Place the sickle against the ground.

2552
01:27:58,119 --> 01:28:00,189
Press it down and pull.

2553
01:28:00,189 --> 01:28:01,589
It shouldn't stick out like this.

2554
01:28:01,589 --> 01:28:02,929
- Place it against the ground.
- Yes.

2555
01:28:02,929 --> 01:28:03,959
(He tries it again.)

2556
01:28:03,959 --> 01:28:05,189
Then cut it.

2557
01:28:05,829 --> 01:28:06,959
That's it.

2558
01:28:07,429 --> 01:28:08,699
Is this good?

2559
01:28:08,699 --> 01:28:10,829
- You did well.
- Yes. That's great.

2560
01:28:11,529 --> 01:28:13,969
We might mess up the work,

2561
01:28:13,969 --> 01:28:15,399
so I'll do something else.

2562
01:28:15,469 --> 01:28:17,309
- What?
- What? Something else?

2563
01:28:17,969 --> 01:28:19,809
- Like washing the water parsley.
- My goodness.

2564
01:28:20,379 --> 01:28:21,709
You can't be doing this already.

2565
01:28:21,709 --> 01:28:22,779
- I can't?
- No.

2566
01:28:23,079 --> 01:28:24,349
It's going in.

2567
01:28:24,349 --> 01:28:25,349
(The real labor begins.)

2568
01:28:26,279 --> 01:28:29,689
(Skillful moves with 19 years of experience in 2 Days 1 Night)

2569
01:28:30,119 --> 01:28:32,619
(A worker who works slowly and yet diligently)

2570
01:28:33,159 --> 01:28:35,089
(Thanks to their hard work, the basket is filling up quickly.)

2571
01:28:35,089 --> 01:28:36,729
I don't have to lift up the sickle.

2572
01:28:36,729 --> 01:28:38,559
(Thanks to their hard work, the basket is filling up quickly.)

2573
01:28:38,729 --> 01:28:39,729
(Shouting)

2574
01:28:39,999 --> 01:28:41,259
My back is killing me.

2575
01:28:41,759 --> 01:28:43,599
My back really hurts.

2576
01:28:43,599 --> 01:28:44,729
(From working bent over for long, they get a sore back.)

2577
01:28:44,729 --> 01:28:45,969
My back hurts.

2578
01:28:46,599 --> 01:28:48,339
You must have a sore back.

2579
01:28:48,339 --> 01:28:49,969
- I do.
- I knew it.

2580
01:28:49,969 --> 01:28:52,869
(A moment experiencing the hardships of farming)

2581
01:28:53,139 --> 01:28:55,179
Your back will be better after eating water parsley.

2582
01:28:55,179 --> 01:28:56,309
You're right.

2583
01:28:56,309 --> 01:28:57,679
What is water parsley good for?

2584
01:28:57,779 --> 01:29:00,779
Water parsley purifies your blood.

2585
01:29:01,219 --> 01:29:02,819
- It purifies your blood?
- Yes.

2586
01:29:03,249 --> 01:29:05,549
- And it heals the back?
- That's right.

2587
01:29:05,549 --> 01:29:07,189
Your back heals if blood circulation is good.

2588
01:29:07,189 --> 01:29:08,619
- Really?
- Right. It's for blood circulation.

2589
01:29:08,619 --> 01:29:10,089
Your back hurts because your blood circulation isn't good.

2590
01:29:10,089 --> 01:29:11,459
It's because of blood circulation.

2591
01:29:11,459 --> 01:29:12,459
That's right.

2592
01:29:12,459 --> 01:29:13,929
You look really young for your age.

2593
01:29:14,159 --> 01:29:16,229
- You look so young.
- Right.

2594
01:29:16,229 --> 01:29:18,369
I thought you were younger than me.

2595
01:29:18,499 --> 01:29:19,969
- Stop it.
- I thought I was older than you.

2596
01:29:19,969 --> 01:29:21,139
I thought you were younger than me.

2597
01:29:21,139 --> 01:29:22,299
It's because of water parsley.

2598
01:29:22,639 --> 01:29:24,309
Is it because water parsley helps blood circulation?

2599
01:29:24,369 --> 01:29:25,469
That's right.

2600
01:29:26,209 --> 01:29:27,879
Actually, I'm hungry.

2601
01:29:27,879 --> 01:29:29,409
- Right.
- Actually,

2602
01:29:29,579 --> 01:29:31,249
we're supposed to eat before working.

2603
01:29:31,609 --> 01:29:34,449
They didn't even give us food.

2604
01:29:34,749 --> 01:29:37,519
- Joon, hold me.
- Why?

2605
01:29:37,519 --> 01:29:39,319
- Help me up.
- What's wrong?

2606
01:29:39,349 --> 01:29:40,389
Hold me.

2607
01:29:41,759 --> 01:29:42,789
My goodness.

2608
01:29:43,159 --> 01:29:46,529
(It's not easy to move around because of the mud.)

2609
01:29:47,299 --> 01:29:48,799
This is difficult.

2610
01:29:49,129 --> 01:29:50,629
Do you do all the work by yourself?

2611
01:29:50,929 --> 01:29:53,399
I usually do the harvest alone in spring.

2612
01:29:54,469 --> 01:29:57,009
How many years have you been farming water parsley?

2613
01:29:57,069 --> 01:29:59,169
I've been doing this for about 20 years.

2614
01:29:59,169 --> 01:30:01,409
- For 20 years?
- You're a master.

2615
01:30:01,979 --> 01:30:04,379
I did 2 Days 1 Night and you grew water parsley.

2616
01:30:04,379 --> 01:30:05,509
That's right.

2617
01:30:06,349 --> 01:30:08,919
(It's been an hour.)

2618
01:30:09,549 --> 01:30:10,689
You cut it off.

2619
01:30:11,649 --> 01:30:13,359
You're getting the hang of it.

2620
01:30:13,589 --> 01:30:15,319
How good will the blood circulation be?

2621
01:30:15,319 --> 01:30:16,489
(Working non-stop, they almost got three baskets full.)

2622
01:30:17,589 --> 01:30:18,929
We did a lot.

2623
01:30:19,159 --> 01:30:21,329
- Let's wrap things up here.
- Okay.

2624
01:30:21,499 --> 01:30:22,629
Let's go to work.

2625
01:30:22,629 --> 01:30:24,169
- Work?
- The next task?

2626
01:30:24,169 --> 01:30:26,329
- Yes.
- Okay.

2627
01:30:26,329 --> 01:30:27,799
So, they have to...

2628
01:30:27,999 --> 01:30:30,309
- pick all of these out one by one.
- Right.

2629
01:30:30,309 --> 01:30:32,869
I thought they would use a machine.

2630
01:30:32,869 --> 01:30:35,009
Everything is done by hand.

2631
01:30:36,649 --> 01:30:38,349
- I know.
- My goodness.

2632
01:30:38,479 --> 01:30:39,579
It's really interesting.

2633
01:30:39,579 --> 01:30:41,249
It requires a lot of work.

2634
01:30:41,549 --> 01:30:43,749
(They've been working for 2 hours, appreciating farmers' hard work.)

2635
01:30:43,749 --> 01:30:44,889
Hello.

2636
01:30:45,249 --> 01:30:47,189
- Thank you for your hard work.
- Hello.

2637
01:30:47,189 --> 01:30:48,419
- Hello.
- Hello.

2638
01:30:48,789 --> 01:30:50,859
I'm a big fan!

2639
01:30:50,859 --> 01:30:51,989
Hello.

2640
01:30:51,989 --> 01:30:53,399
- You should have a snack now.
- A snack?

2641
01:30:53,399 --> 01:30:56,029
- To thank your hard work, - Yes.

2642
01:30:56,029 --> 01:30:57,629
I prepared a snack.

2643
01:30:57,629 --> 01:30:59,229
- Really?
- That's nice.

2644
01:30:59,229 --> 01:31:01,399
- You can stop it now.
- Okay.

2645
01:31:01,739 --> 01:31:03,369
- Yes!
- We wanted to help.

2646
01:31:03,469 --> 01:31:04,869
- Is this it?
- Can we eat?

2647
01:31:05,439 --> 01:31:07,009
She made suyuk!

2648
01:31:07,009 --> 01:31:09,179
They didn't give us breakfast for a reason.

2649
01:31:09,179 --> 01:31:10,549
- That's right.
- This is...

2650
01:31:10,649 --> 01:31:12,679
Thank you for your hard work.

2651
01:31:12,679 --> 01:31:14,919
This looks amazing already.

2652
01:31:14,919 --> 01:31:16,379
- This is insane.
- All right.

2653
01:31:16,379 --> 01:31:17,689
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2654
01:31:17,689 --> 01:31:18,919
(Thank you for the food. We will enjoy it.)

2655
01:31:19,889 --> 01:31:21,089
My goodness. Look.

2656
01:31:21,659 --> 01:31:22,919
Like this.

2657
01:31:23,159 --> 01:31:24,859
- Like this, with water parsley.
- Like this.

2658
01:31:24,989 --> 01:31:26,289
- That's it.
- The water parsley is good.

2659
01:31:26,289 --> 01:31:27,399
Thank you.

2660
01:31:27,399 --> 01:31:30,669
(Taking a big bite)

2661
01:31:34,739 --> 01:31:36,369
- It's refreshing.
- This is insane.

2662
01:31:36,369 --> 01:31:38,669
I love the scent of water parsley.

2663
01:31:38,809 --> 01:31:40,139
It's really savory.

2664
01:31:40,139 --> 01:31:41,839
(Followed by the savory taste of suyuk)

2665
01:31:42,339 --> 01:31:44,049
The sauce is amazing.

2666
01:31:44,049 --> 01:31:45,049
(The sauce brings all of this together in harmony.)

2667
01:31:45,109 --> 01:31:46,519
It's really delicious.

2668
01:31:47,279 --> 01:31:49,249
- I'll eat it with rice.
- This is amazing.

2669
01:31:50,219 --> 01:31:51,249
The water parsley...

2670
01:31:52,189 --> 01:31:53,419
I'll try the water parsley alone.

2671
01:31:53,919 --> 01:31:55,159
It's also good with rice.

2672
01:31:55,159 --> 01:31:56,559
This is incredible.

2673
01:31:56,589 --> 01:31:58,189
I make sure to eat water parsley...

2674
01:31:58,559 --> 01:32:00,029
for all three meals a day, even without meat.

2675
01:32:00,029 --> 01:32:01,059
(He eats water parsley for all three meals every day.)

2676
01:32:01,229 --> 01:32:03,099
Even eating just water parsley is so delicious.

2677
01:32:03,369 --> 01:32:05,129
Their water parsley is so good.

2678
01:32:05,869 --> 01:32:07,339
It goes really well with rice.

2679
01:32:07,669 --> 01:32:10,439
It tastes even better with more water parsley.

2680
01:32:10,439 --> 01:32:11,669
I know. That's true.

2681
01:32:11,669 --> 01:32:13,239
The more water parsley, the tastier it gets.

2682
01:32:16,079 --> 01:32:17,149
It's really good.

2683
01:32:17,679 --> 01:32:18,709
(It tastes even more delicious after such hard work.)

2684
01:32:18,709 --> 01:32:20,119
The meat is cooked perfectly.

2685
01:32:21,249 --> 01:32:22,779
You'll think of this every spring.

2686
01:32:22,919 --> 01:32:24,719
- Right.
- I know. I will miss this a lot.

2687
01:32:25,649 --> 01:32:27,119
Can I come every spring?

2688
01:32:27,119 --> 01:32:28,289
Of course.

2689
01:32:29,559 --> 01:32:31,429
Do you know what's interesting?

2690
01:32:31,559 --> 01:32:33,899
At first, the amount of meat and water parsley was similar.

2691
01:32:33,929 --> 01:32:35,959
- But we ate all the water parsley.
- Right.

2692
01:32:35,959 --> 01:32:37,999
I'm only eating this.

2693
01:32:37,999 --> 01:32:39,469
- Right.
- This is really delicious.

2694
01:32:39,529 --> 01:32:41,239
- It's so good.
- I know.

2695
01:32:41,239 --> 01:32:42,599
What on earth is this?

2696
01:32:42,599 --> 01:32:44,409
This is truly rewarding.

2697
01:32:44,909 --> 01:32:46,039
It's worth enduring the hard work.

2698
01:32:46,309 --> 01:32:47,409
Thank you so much for today.

2699
01:32:47,409 --> 01:32:49,239
- It's nothing.
- My pleasure.

2700
01:32:49,239 --> 01:32:50,409
I got better after eating water parsley.

2701
01:32:50,409 --> 01:32:51,909
- It doesn't hurt anymore, right?
- No.

2702
01:32:51,909 --> 01:32:53,249
- I'm completely healed.
- I'm glad to hear that.

2703
01:32:53,819 --> 01:32:55,319
- Thank you for today.
- Thank you.

2704
01:32:55,319 --> 01:32:56,519
Thank you.

2705
01:32:57,519 --> 01:32:59,959
Should we give you some more for the other members?

2706
01:32:59,959 --> 01:33:01,359
- No.
- It's okay.

2707
01:33:01,359 --> 01:33:03,529
- They must've left.
- They must be sleeping.

2708
01:33:04,359 --> 01:33:06,259
(Next episode)

2709
01:33:06,659 --> 01:33:09,199
(I had almost nothing but 2 Days 1 Night in my head.)

2710
01:33:11,499 --> 01:33:13,199
(Since this is the variety show I've been waiting for,)

2711
01:33:15,039 --> 01:33:16,739
(I'll pour out everything I've prepared.)

2712
01:33:16,869 --> 01:33:18,639
(Guests? Who are they?)

2713
01:33:19,139 --> 01:33:21,279
(There are 2 guests visiting 2 Days 1 Night?)

2714
01:33:21,779 --> 01:33:23,749
(There's only one reason for appearing in this show.)

2715
01:33:23,909 --> 01:33:25,749
(I'm here to win.)

2716
01:33:26,509 --> 01:33:29,119
(Jung Ho Young versus Sam Kim)

2717
01:33:29,119 --> 01:33:30,889
(The home of delicious food)

2718
01:33:30,889 --> 01:33:32,689
(Unfolding in Mokpo)

2719
01:33:32,749 --> 01:33:34,059
(This round is...)

2720
01:33:34,059 --> 01:33:35,559
(the Infinite Ingredient Inferno.)

2721
01:33:36,259 --> 01:33:39,059
(To get their hands on delicacies from land and sea,)

2722
01:33:39,659 --> 01:33:43,129
(they engage in an infinite competition.)

2723
01:33:43,329 --> 01:33:45,329
(And followed by...)

2724
01:33:45,329 --> 01:33:47,099
(an infinite cooking inferno)

2725
01:33:47,139 --> 01:33:48,569
(The fish fell apart!)

2726
01:33:49,439 --> 01:33:52,139
(Who will be the final winner?)

2727
01:33:53,539 --> 01:33:55,309
(This is so good. What is this?)

2728
01:33:55,479 --> 01:33:58,679
(Revealed exclusively on KBS on March 29)

2729
01:33:58,709 --> 01:34:00,549
They're focusing more on just watching than on guessing.

2730
01:34:00,549 --> 01:34:01,845
(See you next week.)
